0
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,000
根据无聊老生字幕制作 by summerheat

1
00:00:40,875 --> 00:00:43,962
战争开始之前的地球
JACK: Earth, before the war.

2
00:00:45,588 --> 00:00:48,717
在我出生之前的纽约
New York, before I was born.

3
00:00:49,843 --> 00:00:53,847
这些画面只出现在相片里
A place I've only seen pictures of.

4
00:00:54,347 --> 00:00:55,598
我认识你
I know you...

5
00:00:55,890 --> 00:00:57,726
却从未谋面
But we've never met.

6
00:00:59,144 --> 00:01:00,770
我和你在一起
I'm with you...

7
00:01:01,730 --> 00:01:04,315
却不知你的名字
But I don't know your name.

8
00:01:06,234 --> 00:01:10,780
我知道我在做梦，感觉却如此真实
I know I'm dreaming. But it feels like more than that.

9
00:01:12,449 --> 00:01:14,743
就像是我的记忆
It feels like a memory.

10
00:01:17,036 --> 00:01:19,080
怎么会这样
How can that be?

11
00:01:28,882 --> 00:01:32,177
2077年3月14日
March 14th, 2077.

12
00:01:32,343 --> 00:01:35,388
距离记忆清除整整五年
Five years since the mandatory memory wipe.

13
00:01:35,555 --> 00:01:38,516
我仍然被这些梦折磨着
And I'm still haunted by these dreams.

14
00:01:41,478 --> 00:01:43,980
维多利亚奉命跟我在一起
Victoria and I were assigned together.

15
00:01:44,147 --> 00:01:48,485
两周之后 我们将完成这里的任务 跟其他人会合
In two weeks, our mission here will be finished, and we'll join the others.

16
00:01:49,277 --> 00:01:52,155
我常有的疑问 她没有
But the questions I ask, she doesn't.

17
00:01:52,322 --> 00:01:55,325
我一直有的困惑 她也没有
The things I wonder about, she won't.

18
00:01:56,618 --> 00:02:00,371
五十年前 拾荒者摧毁了我们的月球
It's been half a century since the scavengers destroyed our moon.

19
00:02:00,538 --> 00:02:05,001
他们的星球即将毁灭 便把目光盯向我们
Forced to leave their own dying planet, they came to take ours.

20
00:02:05,168 --> 00:02:08,338
没有了月球 地球陷入了一片混乱
Without the moon, the Earth was thrown into chaos.

21
00:02:08,505 --> 00:02:10,840
地震把城市摧毁
Earthquakes toppled cities within hours.

22
00:02:11,508 --> 00:02:14,302
海啸吞噬了一切
Tsunamis wiped out what remained.

23
00:02:14,469 --> 00:02:16,513
入侵随后而来
Then came the invasion.

24
00:02:17,430 --> 00:02:19,682
无奈之下
We did what we had to do.

25
00:02:20,183 --> 00:02:22,268
我们动用了核武器
We used the nukes.

26
00:02:23,853 --> 00:02:27,440
我们赢得了战争 却失去了自己的星球
We won the war, but lost the planet.

27
00:02:27,649 --> 00:02:32,528
地球被严重污染 已经不适合人类居住
Left it contaminated. Most of it uninhabitable.

28
00:02:32,904 --> 00:02:36,658
人类别无选择 只能离开地球
What remained of humanity had to leave the Earth.

29
00:02:37,116 --> 00:02:40,829
我们建造了泰特 我们的指挥中心
We built the Tet, our mission control.

30
00:02:40,954 --> 00:02:44,374
临时空间站 准备移居泰坦星
A temporary space station before the migration to Titan,

31
00:02:44,541 --> 00:02:46,543
土星最大的卫星
Saturn's largest moon.

32
00:02:46,709 --> 00:02:48,294
所有人都过去了
Everyone's there now.

33
00:02:48,878 --> 00:02:51,923
只剩两个人
Well, almost everyone.

34
00:02:52,632 --> 00:02:56,636
维多利亚和我有任务
Until our tour is complete, Vika and I do our job.

35
00:02:56,803 --> 00:02:58,388
我们保卫钻水平台
We protect the hydro rigs,

36
00:02:58,555 --> 00:03:00,473
它把地球上的海水
which convert Earth's sea water

37
00:03:00,598 --> 00:03:02,559
转化成新领地所需的混合能源
into fusion energy for the new colony.

38
00:03:02,725 --> 00:03:05,144
人类的生存关乎于此
The survival of humanity depends on it.

39
00:03:08,398 --> 00:03:09,399
(CHUCKLES)

40
00:03:10,483 --> 00:03:11,734
谢谢你的咖啡
Thank you for the coffee.

41
00:03:11,901 --> 00:03:15,947
拾荒者的军队一直骚扰我们
Remnants of the scavenger army continue to disrupt the operation.

42
00:03:16,239 --> 00:03:18,533
他们夜间偷袭我们的无人机
They attack our drones at night,

43
00:03:18,658 --> 00:03:20,910
白天试图杀掉我们
and try to kill me during the day.

44
00:03:21,327 --> 00:03:24,247
没完没了 不知道为什么
There's still fight in them, but I don't know why.

45
00:03:25,665 --> 00:03:28,167
指挥中心说我们两个干得不错
Mission says we have done well.

46
00:03:28,501 --> 00:03:32,005
我们是一对默契的搭档
That we are an effective team.

47
00:03:41,931 --> 00:03:44,183
维多利亚是我的通讯联络官
Vika's my communications officer.

48
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:46,352
她负责照顾我
She keeps an eye on me.

49
00:03:47,145 --> 00:03:49,188
我负责维护无人机
I handle drone maintenance.

50
00:03:49,772 --> 00:03:52,275
无人机则监视一切
The drones watch everything.

51
00:03:53,276 --> 00:03:58,498
维多利亚很期待撤离 我却不确定
Vika can't wait to go. Me, I'm not so sure.

52
00:03:58,948 --> 00:04:01,117
我无法抹去对地球的感觉
I can't shake the feeling that Earth,

53
00:04:01,242 --> 00:04:03,411
尽管已无法挽回 
in spite of all that's happened...

54
00:04:03,578 --> 00:04:06,164
地球 毕竟是我的故乡
Earth is still my home.

55
00:04:26,868 --> 00:04:31,368
《遗落战境》

56
00:04:31,773 --> 00:04:33,858
杰克・哈珀 设备维护师49号
Jack Harper, Tech-49.

57
00:04:34,498 --> 00:04:36,498
（49号 确认）

58
00:05:00,593 --> 00:05:03,012
早啊 鲍勃
Morning, Bob.

59
00:05:10,478 --> 00:05:11,854
呼叫塔台
JACK: (THROUGH SPEAKERS) Tower, comm check.

60
00:05:12,021 --> 00:05:14,857
设备维护师49号开始工作
Drone Maintenance Technician 49, hydro rig support.

61
00:05:15,024 --> 00:05:17,902
系统运行正常
All Bubbleship systems are green.

62
00:05:18,069 --> 00:05:19,112
可以出发了
I'm good to go.

63
00:05:19,278 --> 00:05:21,572
收到 49号 可以出发 注意安全
Copy, Tech-49, you're cleared.
Be careful out there.

64
00:05:21,739 --> 00:05:23,700
- 我很注意 - 才不是呢
Always am. No, you're not.

65
00:05:24,117 --> 00:05:27,948
那好吧 这次一定注意
Yeah, you're right. I gotta work on that.

66
00:05:36,337 --> 00:05:38,381
好了 30秒后接通泰特
All right, Tet's coming online in 30 seconds.

67
00:05:38,548 --> 00:05:41,718
把钻水平台的画面传送给你 确认视野
Relaying hydro rig coordinates now. Confirm visual.

68
00:05:46,347 --> 00:05:49,684
收到 钻水平台正在吸纳海水
I got 'em. Hydro rigs are sucking seawater.

69
00:05:51,185 --> 00:05:52,228
看到了 鲍勃
You got 'em, Bob?

70
00:05:55,023 --> 00:05:56,899
185号无人机正常
Drone 185 looks good.

71
00:06:03,906 --> 00:06:05,700
有两个无人机失去动力
Jack, we've got two drones down.

72
00:06:07,243 --> 00:06:08,244
该死
Shit.

73
00:06:08,411 --> 00:06:09,996
等等 指挥中心上线了
Stand by, Mission coming online.

74
00:06:11,998 --> 00:06:14,083
可以通话了
VICTORIA: And we have Tet contact.

75
00:06:16,753 --> 00:06:18,087
早啊 老板
Morning, boss.

76
00:06:19,380 --> 00:06:21,424
49号塔台 这里是指挥中心
Tower 49, this is Mission Control.

77
00:06:21,591 --> 00:06:23,676
两位早上很愉快吧
How y'all doing this lovely morning?

78
00:06:23,843 --> 00:06:28,438
简直像天堂一样 萨莉 现在上传数据
Another day in paradise, Sally. Uploading data now.

79
00:06:28,442 --> 00:06:31,726
49号工作日志 第1642天 钻水平台维护
49 mission log. Day 1642, hydro rig support.

80
00:06:31,893 --> 00:06:33,770
- 有两个 - 无人机失去动力
I have two... You have two drones offline.

81
00:06:33,936 --> 00:06:35,772
四周安全存在隐患
Perimeter's compromised.

82
00:06:35,938 --> 00:06:38,733
收到 马上通知维护师
Copy that, relaying to Tech. Stand by.

83
00:06:39,776 --> 00:06:43,613
杰克 166号在37号区域失去动力
Jack, 166 is down in Grid 37.

84
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,573
路线设定完毕
Linking to beacon now.

85
00:06:45,782 --> 00:06:47,950
你先到那儿去
You'll go there first.

86
00:06:48,117 --> 00:06:50,745
收到 我去了
Got it. On my way.

87
00:06:52,914 --> 00:06:55,333
49号已经在去37号区域的路上
VICTORIA: Mission, Tech-49 is en route to Grid 37 now.

88
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,502
能用109号无人机完成修复吗
Can you plug that hole with Drone 109?

89
00:06:57,668 --> 00:07:01,778
不行 109号还没修好 正在等待配件
Negative, 109 is in the dock. Still waiting for parts.

90
00:07:01,822 --> 00:07:03,591
杰克 找到那两个无人机 修好它们
Jack better find those drones and get 'em flying.

91
00:07:03,758 --> 00:07:05,968
平台不能整夜暴露着
Those rigs can't be exposed overnight.

92
00:07:07,136 --> 00:07:08,137
明白
Copy that.

93
00:07:13,893 --> 00:07:15,144
(GRUNTS)

94
00:07:30,201 --> 00:07:33,079
最近对166号做过保养吗
SALLY: Tower, didn't he fix 166 recently?

95
00:07:33,246 --> 00:07:35,039
杰克 所有的无人机都保养过
Jack has fixed all the drones recently.

96
00:07:35,206 --> 00:07:36,874
如果我们需要的零件齐备
And, if we had the parts that we've been asking for,

97
00:07:37,041 --> 00:07:38,501
就不会这么捉襟见肘
we wouldn't be running a skeleton crew down here.

98
00:07:38,668 --> 00:07:41,337
我明白 你们尽了最大的努力
Understood. We're doing the best we can.

99
00:07:41,504 --> 00:07:42,672
- 你们不是最佳搭档吗 
Are you an effective team?

100
00:07:43,005 --> 00:07:44,715
- 我们是最佳搭档
We are an effective team.

101
00:07:49,053 --> 00:07:52,265
你们今天的任务是修复166号 找到172号
Your directive today is to rehabilitate 166 and find 172.

102
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:55,518
日落之前 让它们恢复飞行
Get 'em flying by sundown,

103
00:07:55,685 --> 00:07:58,563
等你们到了泰特 我请你俩喝酒
and I'll buy you two a round of drinks when you get up to the Tet.

104
00:07:58,729 --> 00:07:59,981
那你准备好 
You had better be ready, Sally.

105
00:08:00,064 --> 00:08:03,278
两周的时间，我们会记得
Two weeks now, we're keeping track.

106
00:08:02,567 --> 00:08:03,609
(GRUNTS)

107
00:08:03,693 --> 00:08:04,694
Okay.

108
00:08:06,529 --> 00:08:08,781
好了 拜托 伙计 你别光看热闹
Come on, Bob. Work with me, here, buddy.

109
00:08:16,455 --> 00:08:17,915
49号
Tech-49?

110
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:20,543
49号
Tech-49?

111
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,047
杰克
Jack?

112
00:08:25,548 --> 00:08:26,549
收到 塔台
Copy, Tower.

113
00:08:26,716 --> 00:08:28,551
怎么回事 刚才看不见你了
What happened? I lost you for a second.

114
00:08:28,968 --> 00:08:30,136
真的
Really?

115
00:08:31,637 --> 00:08:33,222
正在接近目标
JACK: Coming up on location.

116
00:08:45,985 --> 00:08:46,986
看到它了
There it is.

117
00:08:47,737 --> 00:08:49,739
有战斗过的痕迹
I've got multiple scav kills.

118
00:08:49,906 --> 00:08:52,074
166号经历过一场激战
Drone 166 put up a hell of a fight.

119
00:08:53,242 --> 00:08:54,327
有什么发现吗
Got any movement?

120
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:56,996
没有拾荒者的活动迹象
No sign of scavenger activity.

121
00:08:57,163 --> 00:09:00,416
我这里看不到什么 角度太小了
But I've got limited visibility, here, Jack, due to low angle of Mission.

122
00:09:00,583 --> 00:09:03,688
收到 我下去看看
Copy that. I'm coming in hot.

123
00:09:30,321 --> 00:09:33,324
我要开工了 帮我看着点
Starting repairs. Watch my back.

124
00:09:34,951 --> 00:09:36,661
我看着呢
I always do.

125
00:09:56,398 --> 00:09:58,298
2017年 世界冠军

126
00:09:58,975 --> 00:10:01,310
在书上见过这种运动
You know, I read about this game.

127
00:10:04,105 --> 00:10:06,023
比赛在这儿举行
It was played right here.

128
00:10:06,983 --> 00:10:08,484
最后一届超级碗
The last Super Bowl.

129
00:10:08,651 --> 00:10:10,111
- 别告诉我 又是经典大战
Please don't tell me it was a classic.

130
00:10:10,486 --> 00:10:11,779
- 绝世经典
A classic game.

131
00:10:14,156 --> 00:10:15,157
落后4分
Down by four.

132
00:10:17,535 --> 00:10:21,497
球还在50码线上
The ball was on the 50-yard line.

133
00:10:21,664 --> 00:10:23,165
就剩下几秒钟的时间了
Seconds left on the clock.

134
00:10:25,334 --> 00:10:26,961
球飞起来
The ball is snapped,

135
00:10:27,795 --> 00:10:29,213
四分卫失手了
and the QB fumbles.

136
00:10:31,173 --> 00:10:32,717
悲剧啊
Disaster.

137
00:10:33,718 --> 00:10:35,636
看起来比赛就要结束
Looks like the game is over.

138
00:10:37,513 --> 00:10:39,181
所有芯体位置都不对
I'm reading the whole central core off-alignment.

139
00:10:39,348 --> 00:10:41,350
你手边没有合适的工具
You don't have the necessary tools down there.

140
00:10:41,517 --> 00:10:43,144
新的燃料电池又不匹配
And a new fuel cell is not going to fix that.

141
00:10:46,522 --> 00:10:49,358
- 四分卫掉过头 捡起脱手的球
But this QB runs back, and picks up his own fumble.

142
00:10:49,525 --> 00:10:50,693
 - 等等 你在干什么
Hold on, what did you just do?

143
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:53,404
对方许多球员像一面墙压过来
There's a wall of linebackers closing in on him.

144
00:10:55,323 --> 00:11:00,218
他把球扔了出去 也不管谁能接到
So, he throws a long ball with no idea who is at the other end.

145
00:11:00,369 --> 00:11:02,038
真是个奇迹
A Hail Mary.

146
00:11:03,998 --> 00:11:06,125
八万名观众都起立
Eighty-thousand people on their feet,

147
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:08,419
看球在空中飞过 
watching this ball sail through the air.

148
00:11:09,587 --> 00:11:15,384
在前场的是个新手 三队的外接球员
Downfield is a rookie wide receiver, third string.

149
00:11:15,718 --> 00:11:18,054
他从人群中轻轻一跃
He just leaps out of the pack.

150
00:11:19,722 --> 00:11:21,599
触底得分
Touchdown!

151
00:11:21,974 --> 00:11:23,726
(IMITATES CHEERING)

152
00:11:40,701 --> 00:11:41,786
西边 发现情况
Contact! West contact!

153
00:11:44,789 --> 00:11:46,540
杰克
VICTORIA: Jack?

154
00:11:47,124 --> 00:11:48,250
没事 维多利亚
It's okay, Vika.

155
00:11:49,335 --> 00:11:51,087
是一只狗
It's just a dog.

156
00:11:58,344 --> 00:11:59,345
Hey.

157
00:12:00,054 --> 00:12:01,889
你快走吧 快离开这儿
Now, go on. You gotta get out of here.

158
00:12:03,182 --> 00:12:04,266
走
Go on, get!

159
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:06,560
离开这儿 走
Get out of here! Go!

160
00:12:14,944 --> 00:12:16,779
49号 杰克・哈珀
Tech-49, Jack Harper.

161
00:12:43,806 --> 00:12:45,724
不用客气
You're welcome.

162
00:12:45,808 --> 00:12:46,809
(SCOFFS)

163
00:12:48,644 --> 00:12:51,772
166号恢复正常
166 is back online.

164
00:12:59,655 --> 00:13:03,668
今天又被击落两架 一个月被偷了10块燃料电池
Two drones shot down today. Ten fuel cells stolen in just over a month.

165
00:13:03,742 --> 00:13:05,995
这些家伙越来越嚣张了
These scavs are getting bolder.

166
00:13:06,162 --> 00:13:08,164
平台正在吸纳海水
VICTORIA: Well, the hydro rigs are taking all the water.

167
00:13:08,664 --> 00:13:11,417
我们走后 他们只有灰尘和射线
Once we're gone, they'll have nothing but dust and radiation.

168
00:13:12,168 --> 00:13:13,836
狗屁逻辑
JACK: This is bullshit.

169
00:13:14,253 --> 00:13:18,507
我们打赢了 却要被迫撤离
We won the war. Now we have to leave.

170
00:13:20,801 --> 00:13:22,511
再有两个星期
Two more weeks, Jack.

171
00:13:23,179 --> 00:13:25,514
我们就可以去泰坦星了
Then we'll be on our way to Titan.

172
00:13:26,849 --> 00:13:27,850
对
Yep.

173
00:13:29,185 --> 00:13:31,479
那个无人机还在某处
That drone is out there somewhere.

174
00:13:33,355 --> 00:13:35,024
得想办法找到它
We just have to find it.

175
00:13:35,441 --> 00:13:38,527
没有灯标 找它无异于大海捞针
Without a beacon, that's like finding a needle in a haystack.

176
00:13:38,861 --> 00:13:40,196
(CHUCKLES)

177
00:13:46,327 --> 00:13:49,205
所以得当步兵了
So we go to our ground game.

178
00:15:30,764 --> 00:15:34,828
塔台 我找到172号了
Tower, I've located 172

179
00:15:35,394 --> 00:15:37,563
在一个大洞里
down a sinkhole.

180
00:15:37,730 --> 00:15:39,815
看不见 但能听到
No visual, but I can hear it.

181
00:15:39,982 --> 00:15:42,067
我这里角度很差 只能看到你 
Tet's so far off angle, I can barely see you.

182
00:15:42,234 --> 00:15:43,444
它怎么样
How's it look?

183
00:15:44,778 --> 00:15:48,407
还好 上面没发现敌人的迹象
It's good, it's good. There's no sign of scav activity on top.

184
